cuisine: Thai
---

olive oil
1 head broccoli
1 packet Diced Chicken
1 packet Mild Thai Red Curry Paste
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 packet coconut milk
½ tbs soy sauce
2 cup water
1 packet Udon Noodles
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 sachet Crispy Shallots
1 packet Diced Bacon

• In a large saucepan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. When oil is hot, cook diced chicken and broccoli florets, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 6-7 minutes.
• Reduce heat to medium-high heat, add mild Thai red curry paste and sweet soy seasoning and cook, stirring, until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add coconut milk, soy sauce and the water. Stir to combine and bring to a simmer.

• Add udon noodles, until tender, 1-2 minutes. In the last minute of cook time, gently stir noodles with a fork to separate.

• Add baby spinach leaves and stir to combine. Season to taste.

• Divide mild Thai red curry chicken and noodle soup between bowls.
• Sprinkle over crispy shallots. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Add the finishing touch by sprinkling over the crisp!